ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An entity such as an individual, company, institution, group, or organization which takes responsibility for the initiation, management, and/or financing of a clinical study. The sponsor does not actually conduct the investigation unless the sponsor is a sponsor-investigator. A person other than an individual (e.g., corporation or agency) that uses one or more of its own employees to conduct research it has initiated is considered to be a sponsor, and the employees are considered to be investigators. [21 CFR P.50.3(k)] [21 CFR P.50.102(j)] [21 CFR P.312.3]

Concepts.definition: An entity such as an individual, company, institution, group, or organization which takes responsibility for the initiation, management, and/or financing of a clinical study. The sponsor does not actually conduct the investigation unless the sponsor is a sponsor-investigator. A person other than an individual (e.g., corporation or agency) that uses one or more of its own employees to conduct research it has initiated is considered to be a sponsor, and the employees are considered to be investigators. [21 CFR P.50.3(k)] [21 CFR P.50.102(j)] [21 CFR P.312.3]

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: a researcher in a clinical trial or clinical study.

Concepts.definition: An individual who conducts scientific research. In a clinical setting this individual actually conducts and/or supervises the clinical investigation and study-related procedures.  The investigator monitors the safety of the trial subjects and investigational staff (under whose immediate direction an agent is administered or dispensed to a subject).  The investigator collects and analyses data and study documents, and provides reports in compliance with applicable requirements.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person who is employed by a study sponsor or by a contract research organization (CRO), operates independently from the clinical study site and functions as a monitor, and/or auditor, and/or a project director within a particular trial or institution.

Concepts.definition: A person who is employed by a study sponsor or by a contract research organization (CRO), operates independently from the clinical study site and functions as a monitor, and/or auditor, and/or a project director within a particular trial or institution.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person to whom a clinical investigator delegates a few of the routine administrative requirements of a protocol. The duties and responsibilities of a clinical research coordinator may vary across different infrastructures. Generally, the coordinator manages the subject's clinical trial participation and provides a vital linkage between the subject, the investigator, and the sponsor.

Concepts.definition: A person to whom a clinical investigator delegates a few of the routine administrative requirements of a protocol. The duties and responsibilities of a clinical research coordinator may vary across different infrastructures. Generally, the coordinator manages the subject's clinical trial participation and provides a vital linkage between the subject, the investigator, and the sponsor.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A matter or an individual that is observed, analyzed, examined, investigated, experimented upon, or/and treated in the course of a particular study.

Concepts.definition: A matter or an individual that is observed, analyzed, examined, investigated, experimented upon, or/and treated in the course of a particular study.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The primary person in charge of the care of a patient, usually a family member or a designated health care professional.

Concepts.definition: The primary person in charge of the care of a patient, usually a family member or a designated health care professional.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Sibling; a person's brother or sister.

Concepts.definition: A person's brother or sister.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Indicates a person who is a member of an unmarried couple, including same sex couples, living together in longstanding relationships, that are registered or unregistered.

Concepts.definition: Indicates a person who is a member of an unmarried couple, including same sex couples, living together in longstanding relationships, that are registered or unregistered.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A mother or a father; the immediate progenitor.

Concepts.definition: A mother or a father; an immediate progenitor.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An individual who is authorized under applicable State or local law to consent on behalf of a child or incapable person to general medical care including participation in clinical research.

Concepts.definition: An individual who is authorized under applicable State or local law to consent on behalf of a child or incapable person to general medical care including participation in clinical research.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person qualified to be engaged in activity directed at preservation of mental and physical health by diseases prevention and treatment as a source of livelihood.

Concepts.definition: A person qualified to be engaged in activity directed at preservation of mental and physical health by diseases prevention and treatment as a source of livelihood.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person's partner in marriage.

Concepts.definition: A person's partner in marriage.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A member of the fundamental unit of society designed primarily to regulate sexual behavior and reproduce, nurture, protect, and socialize the youngs, traditionally organized around kinship ties, descend from the common progenitor or related by marriage or by a feeling of closeness; or of any of various social units differing from but regarded as equivalent to the traditional family.

Concepts.definition: Any of the individuals who are descended from a common progenitor, related by marriage or other legal tie, or by a feeling of closeness.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person or agency that promotes or exchanges goods or services for money; a seller.

Concepts.definition: A person or agency that promotes or exchanges goods or services for money; a seller.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An individual qualified to perform an evaluation who is masked from a subject's data in order to minimize bias or maximize consistency and quality.

Concepts.definition: An individual qualified to perform an evaluation who is masked from a subject's data in order to minimize bias or maximize consistency and quality.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The person who manages an interview and asks the questions.

Concepts.definition: The person who manages an interview and asks the questions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An external committee whose purpose is to evaluate study data and decide whether a study endpoint or other criterion has been met.

Concepts.definition: An external committee whose purpose is to evaluate study data and decide whether a study endpoint or other criterion has been met.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person whom an individual knows, likes, and trusts.

Concepts.definition: A person whom an individual knows, likes, and trusts.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An individual that presides over and arbitrates disputes between individuals or organizations.

Concepts.definition: An individual that presides over and arbitrates disputes between individuals or organizations.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An individual's biological or non-biological first generation offspring, including but not limited to biological children (including those born outside of marriage), adopted children, step children, and foster children.

Concepts.definition: An individual's biological or non-biological first generation offspring, including but not limited to biological children (including those born outside of marriage), adopted children, step children, and foster children.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A type of advance directive that gives a person the authority to make decisions for another individual. It becomes active when that person loses the ability to make decisions for him- or herself.

Concepts.definition: A type of advance directive that gives a person the authority to make decisions for another individual. It becomes active when that person loses the ability to make decisions for him- or herself.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A gender-neutral term for a person's partner in an intimate or romantic relationship without disclosing or presuming marital status or sexual orientation.

Concepts.definition: A gender-neutral term for a person's partner in an intimate or romantic relationship without disclosing or presuming marital status or sexual orientation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An individual qualified in a profession outside the healthcare field.

Concepts.definition: An individual qualified in a profession outside the healthcare field.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Any individual member of the clinical trial team designated and supervised by the investigator at a trial site to perform critical trial-related procedures and/or to make important trial-related decisions (e.g., associates, residents, research fellows).

Concepts.definition: Any individual member of the clinical trial team designated and supervised by the investigator at a trial site to perform critical trial-related procedures and/or to make important trial-related decisions (e.g., associates, residents, research fellows).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An investigator who is responsible for all aspects of the conduct of a study.

Concepts.definition: An investigator who is responsible for all aspects of the conduct of a study.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A physician who specializes in the diagnosis and treatment of heart disorders.

Concepts.definition: A physician who specializes in the diagnosis and treatment of heart disorders.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A health care professional trained in the visualization of structures too small to be seen by the naked eye, using various microscopic techniques.

Concepts.definition: A health care professional trained in the visualization of structures too small to be seen by the naked eye, using various microscopic techniques.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Any individual qualified to perform an evaluation.

Concepts.definition: Any individual qualified to perform an evaluation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A physician with a Doctor of Optometry degree (or analogous) that specializes in the diagnosis and treatment of eye disorders.

Concepts.definition: A physician with a Doctor of Optometry degree (or analogous) that specializes in the diagnosis and treatment of eye disorders.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A physician specializing in medical diagnosis based on both the macroscopic and the microscopic changes to tissues and organs caused by a disease.

Concepts.definition: A physician specializing in medical diagnosis based on both the macroscopic and the microscopic changes to tissues and organs caused by a disease.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A physician specializing in the diagnosis of both the cause of death and the manner of death of another human being.

Concepts.definition: A physician specializing in the diagnosis of both the cause of death and the manner of death of another human being.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A pediatrician who specializes in diagnosing and treating developmental and behavioral disorders in children.

Concepts.definition: A pediatrician who specializes in diagnosing and treating developmental and behavioral disorders in children.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A psychologist who specializes in diagnosing and treating emotional and behavioral problems associated with developmental delay or disability.

Concepts.definition: A psychologist who specializes in diagnosing and treating emotional and behavioral problems associated with developmental delay or disability.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A neurologist that specializes in diagnosing and treating children.

Concepts.definition: A neurologist that specializes in diagnosing and treating children.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating diseases and disorders of the nervous system.

Concepts.definition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating diseases and disorders of the nervous system.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Pathologist is a doctor specialized in medical diagnosis based on the macroscopic and microscopic study of structural changes of tissues and organs caused by the disease.

Concepts.definition: Any physician whose career is devoted to the study of pathology.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor concerned with the diagnosis and treatment of skin conditions.

Concepts.definition: A doctor concerned with the diagnosis and treatment of skin conditions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating conditions affecting the endocrine system.

Concepts.definition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating conditions affecting the endocrine system.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: (on-KOL-o-jist) A doctor who specializes in treating cancer.  Some oncologists specialize in a particular type of cancer treatment.  For example, a radiation oncologist specializes in treating cancer with radiation.

Concepts.definition: A physician who specializes in the diagnosis and treatment of cancer.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating eye problems, including injury and disease.

Concepts.definition: A physician with a Doctor of Medicine or Doctor of Osteopathic Medicine degree (or analogous) who specializes in diagnosing and treating eye disorders, including more complex disorders that require surgery.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in treating diseases of the ear, nose, and throat.

Concepts.definition: A doctor who specializes in treating diseases of the ear, nose, and throat.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: (RAY-dee-OL-o-jist) A doctor who specializes in creating and interpreting pictures of areas inside the body. The pictures are produced with x-rays, sound waves, or other types of energy.

Concepts.definition: A physician who specializes in the diagnostic and/or therapeutic uses of radiation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in diseases of the urinary organs in females and the urinary and sex organs in males.

Concepts.definition: A doctor who specializes in diseases of the urinary organs in females and the urinary and sex organs in males.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating diseases and disorders of the blood and blood-forming organs.

Concepts.definition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating diseases and disorders of the blood and blood-forming organs.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A specialist in internal medicine

Concepts.definition: A specialist in internal medicine

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The specific medical individual, usually a radiologist, who looks at and interprets a medical image.

Concepts.definition: The specific medical individual, usually a radiologist, who looks at and interprets a medical image.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An individual trained and certified to apply knowledge of the concepts, principles, and practices of physical therapy for the treatment or prevention of physical disability or disease. Physical therapist plans and carries out treatment utilizing therapeutic exercise, massage, and physical agents such as air, water, electricity, sound, and radiant energy; performs tests and measurements involving manual or electrical means; and interpret results. Therapist also devises adaptations of equipment to meet the specific needs of patients.

Concepts.definition: An individual trained and certified to apply knowledge of the concepts, principles, and practices of physical therapy for the treatment or prevention of physical disability or disease. Physical therapist plans and carries out treatment utilizing therapeutic exercise, massage, and physical agents such as air, water, electricity, sound, and radiant energy; performs tests and measurements involving manual or electrical means; and interpret results. Therapist also devises adaptations of equipment to meet the specific needs of patients.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor trained in radiology who specializes in creating and interpreting pictures of the nervous system. The pictures are produced using forms of radiation, such as x-rays, sound waves, or other types of energy.

Concepts.definition: A doctor trained in radiology who specializes in creating and interpreting pictures of the nervous system. The pictures are produced using forms of radiation, such as x-rays, sound waves, or other types of energy.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A person authorized through certification to perform an evaluation or assessment.

Concepts.definition: A person authorized through certification to perform an evaluation or assessment.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A type of radiologist who specializes in procedures using radioactive materials to diagnose and/or treat patients.

Concepts.definition: A type of radiologist who specializes in procedures using radioactive materials to diagnose and/or treat patients.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A scientist who studies and/or works in the field of pharmacokinetics.

Concepts.definition: A scientist who studies and/or works in the field of pharmacokinetics.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: No value exists.

Concepts.definition: No value exists.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating diseases and disorders of the female reproductive organs.

Concepts.definition: A doctor who specializes in diagnosing and treating diseases and disorders of the female reproductive organs.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A health professional educated in the discipline of midwifery, including care of women during pregnancy, child birth, and post-partum care.

Concepts.definition: A health professional educated in the discipline of midwifery, including care of women during pregnancy, child birth, and post-partum care.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A physician that specializes in the treatment of women as it relates to pregnancy, child birth, and post-partum care.

Concepts.definition: A physician that specializes in the treatment of women as it relates to pregnancy, child birth, and post-partum care.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cardiologist who specializes in the treatment of children.

Concepts.definition: A cardiologist who specializes in the treatment of children.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A health professional educated in the discipline of sonography.

Concepts.definition: A health professional educated in the discipline of sonography.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A trained non-medical health professional who specializes in the identification, testing, habilitation and rehabilitation of hearing loss and other auditory and balance disorders. Particularly, an audiologist may be involved in diagnostic and screening procedures to determine hearing deficits, as well as in assessment of amplification devices and instruction in their care, training in speechreading, and may serve as consultant to government and industry on issues concerning environmental, noise-induced hearing loss. Certification requirements for clinical audiology professional are currently defined at a single level - Certificate of Clinical Competency.

Concepts.definition: A trained non-medical health professional who specializes in the identification, testing, habilitation and rehabilitation of hearing loss and other auditory and balance disorders. Particularly, an audiologist may be involved in diagnostic and screening procedures to determine hearing deficits, as well as in assessment of amplification devices and instruction in their care, training in speechreading, and may serve as consultant to government and industry on issues concerning environmental, noise-induced hearing loss. Certification requirements for clinical audiology professional are currently defined at a single level - Certificate of Clinical Competency.
